This paper discusses the High Level Architecture (HLA) Evolved modular Federation Object Model (FOM), which is a software engineering concept related to distributed systems and simulation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also discusses the impact on HLA standards, which suggests a possible fit with cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also mentions the importance of facilitating composable simulation, which could be related to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses merging processes and rules, which could be related to cs.PL (Programming Languages).
